40|$|We {{investigate}} the permutation modules associated {{to the set}} of faces of the n-dimensional hyperoctahedron, denoted H^n. We show that certain <b>spectral</b> <b>decompositions</b> of these permutation modules determine their irreducibles B_n - submodules completely. The same method also describes the exact relationship between the face modules in any two dimensions 0 ≤ t ≤ k ≤ n. Applications of this technique include a rank formula for the incidence rank of the t-faces versus the k-faces of H^n and a characterization of (t,k,l) -designs on H^n. We also discuss the connection of <b>spectral</b> <b>decompositions</b> to the classical association schemes on Hn and prove an orbit theorem for subgroups of the hyperoctahedral group {{on the set of}} faces of H^n. Comment: 23 page...|$|R
