40|$|The {{investigation}} of influencing special local {{features of the}} coefficients in the elliptic differential operators considered both in the limited field and in the whole space, on the spectral characteristics of these operators including on the absolute and even divergence of the <b>spectral</b> <b>decompositions</b> and also on the evaluations of the Schroedinger operator resolvent on the continuous spectrum has been made. The accurate evaluations of the fundamental solution and accurate conditions for absolute and even divergence of the <b>spectral</b> <b>decompositions</b> of the operators with special feature have been obtained. The new evaluations of the resolvent on the continuous spectrum of the Schroedinger operator with singular potential have been obtained, these evaluations have been applied for solution of the inverse problems on the potential restoration according to the scattering data. Available from VNTIC / VNTIC - Scientific & Technical Information Centre of RussiaSIGLERURussian Federatio...|$|R
